Here's the function I currently use to work around broken strings:

```python
def fix_encoding(s):
    """Fix bad encoding with an ugly hack

    https://github.com/thisbejim/Pyrebase/issues/103
    https://github.com/thisbejim/Pyrebase/issues/81
    """
    try:
        # fix broken string
        return s.encode('latin-1').decode('utf8')
    except UnicodeError:
        # this is for the time when Google or Pyrebase would fix the bug
        return ftfy.fix_encoding(s)
```

