I have a similar use case and currying does work for this, however I am now running into the problem described in issues #285 and #405. Even when using named functions, still seeing that issue where active sorted column is not showing correctly:

```javascript
$scope.sort = function sortParam(index) {
    return function sortValue(value) {
        return value[index];
    };
};
```

Doing this WITHOUT currying is working as expected:

```javascript
$scope.sort1 = function sortValue1(value) {
        return value[1];
    };
};

$scope.sort2 = function sortValue2(value) {
        return value[2];
    };
};
```

I have [modified a Plunk](http://plnkr.co/edit/vgwE5P?p=preview) from issue #405, where you can see it broken.

Can you please provide any feedback? Thanks

