@bertildaniel what you want to achieve can now easily be done by adding a default value to the new parameter that the function expects in TG2.3.8

For example, if you want to have `?user_name=value` appear into the `user` parameter you would just do:

```
def replace_user_name_with_user(remainder, params):
   params['user'] = params.get('user_name')

@before_validate(replace_user_name_with_user)
def myaction(self, user=None):
   return str(user)
```

Then the dispatcher would have no problems with the missing user argument as it has a default value and  you would rename the parameter before it gets validated or used.

On TG2.3.7 and before you could do the same, but just needed to add `**kwargs` to your action method.
That's actually done often by tgext.crud through `@map_primary_keys` and `@apply_default_filters` decorators https://github.com/TurboGears/tgext.crud/blob/master/tgext/crud/controller.py#L464

